@node Main "Tri_Add - Documentation"

                             'Tri_Add' V1.06
                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  'Tri_Add' is a mathematical @{" puzzle " link play} where you add the numbers of a
pyramid-like board. Here's a simplified example of a typical game (note
that the actual game has 10 rows instead of the 4 rows displayed here):

                             @{"2" link play}
                            @{"7" link play}@{"4" link play}
                           @{"5" link play}@{"8" link play}@{"1" link play}
                          @{"2" link play}@{"4" link play}@{"3" link play}@{"9" link play}

  You start from the top and you go down on each row. The lower tile you
choose must always be linked either at left or at right from the upper
choosen tile. As you descend in the pyramid, the selected tiles form a
'path'.

  The game adds the total from the selected tiles and displays it under
the pyramid. When you get to the lowest row and your total equals the
total of the game, you win.

  Have fun!

