@node features "Features"

                               Features

-There is no complex installation: just run the game and play!

-Tri_Add is a "Workbench" game, so it's meant to be played on the
 Workbench screen. The game window can be resized up to a maximum of
 640 x 400 pixels, and the game is redisplayed according to the new
 window size. If the window is too small, it will be automatically
 resized to an adequate displayable size.

-As the game uses as little of the computer's ressources as possible,
 you can run other applications, games, etc. at the same time.

-Tri_Add works on all Amigas with Workbench 1.3 or higher.

@endnode

@node histo "History"

                               Versions History

  What follows are the various updates that were done since the first
version of this game.

1.0: -First release.

1.01: -No more blitting objects, now the game draws the shapes with simple
       OS friendly commands (it is more usable for systems using Amiga
       emulators such as MorphOS, Amithlon, etc.).
      -Other changes were made to the program code.

1.02: -Some minor changes were made to the program code: the routine to
       generate the main game window has been revised.

1.03: -Bugfix: The game could crash in some circumstances when its window
       was resized.

1.04: -Some cosmetic changes were made: the buttons have been redrawn, the 
       pull-down menus were enhanced.
      -Various changes were made to the program code.

1.05: -Now the game displays the number of moves that were made to complete
       a game.
      -Some minor changes were made to the program code (some game display
       routines were reworked, unneeded program code was removed, etc.).

1.06: -Lots of changes or improvements have been made:
        -The routine that add the total from the selected tiles has been
         revised.
        -The game board tiles have been redrawn.
        -The routine that displays the game buttons and other stats have
         been reworked.
        -The routine that generates the game window size has been revised,
         again! (I hope its the last time... until the next time ;)
        -The 'About' window has been slightly changed and its 'Okay' button
         has been removed. 
        -Various other minor changes have been made.

@endnode

@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Tri_Add" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. 

                             How to play?

  To play, just click on a tile. If you start a game, click on the
uppermost tile in the pyramid and click on the lower tiles until you
reach the bottom of the board. The lower tile you choose must always
be linked either at left or at right from the upper choosen tile. As
you descend in the pyramid, the selected tiles form a 'path'.

  The game adds the total from the selected tiles and displays it
under the pyramid. When you get to the lowest row and your total
equals the total of the game (indicated by the label 'Total to get:'
at the right of the board), you win, then Tri_Angle will display the
number of moves you made to complete the game.

  You can go back anytime or even restart from the top of the
pyramid. If you restart from a tile lower than the top, the new
choosen tiles must always be linked with an upper selected one.
When you select a tile that is located higher than the last
choosen tiles, all the path created earlier from that row will
be erased.

  You can restart the game anytime by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub}
button (or with the Right-Amiga + "N" key combination).

  Have fun!

@endnode

